{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdea-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7701"},"text":"§ 7701.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appellate procedures","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdeb-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" An employee, or applicant for employment, may submit an appeal to the Merit Systems Protection Board from any action which is appealable to the Board under any law, rule, or regulation. An appellant shall have the right—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdec-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to a hearing for which a transcript will be kept; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fded-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to be represented by an attorney or other representative.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Appeals shall be processed in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdee-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdef-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Board may hear any case appealed to it or may refer the case to an administrative law judge appointed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3105"},"text":"section 3105 of this title","children":[],"tail":" or other employee of the Board designated by the Board to hear such cases, except that in any case involving a removal from the service, the case shall be heard by the Board, an employee experienced in hearing appeals, or an administrative law judge. The Board, administrative law judge, or other employee (as the case may be) shall make a decision after receipt of the written representations of the parties to the appeal and after opportunity for a hearing under subsection (a)(1) of this section. A copy of the decision shall be furnished to each party to the appeal and to the Office of Personnel Management."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" If an employee or applicant for employment is the prevailing party in an appeal under this subsection, the employee or applicant shall be granted the relief provided in the decision effective upon the making of the decision, and remaining in effect pending the outcome of any petition for review under subsection (e), unless—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf2-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the deciding official determines that the granting of such relief is not appropriate; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/A/ii/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the relief granted in the decision provides that such employee or applicant shall return or be present at the place of employment during the period pending the outcome of any petition for review under subsection (e); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/A/ii/II"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the employing agency, subject to the provisions of subparagraph (B), determines that the return or presence of such employee or applicant is unduly disruptive to the work environment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If an agency makes a determination under subparagraph (A)(ii)(II) that prevents the return or presence of an employee at the place of employment, such employee shall receive pay, compensation, and all other benefits as terms and conditions of employment during the period pending the outcome of any petition for review under subsection (e).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf7-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in the provisions of this paragraph may be construed to require any award of back pay or attorney fees be paid before the decision is final.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" With respect to an appeal from an adverse action covered by subchapter V of chapter 75, authority to mitigate the personnel action involved shall be available, subject to the same standards as would apply in an appeal involving an action covered by subchapter II of chapter 75 with respect to which mitigation authority under this section exists.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdf9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdfa-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the decision of the agency shall be sustained under subsection (b) only if the agency’s decision—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdfb-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of an action based on unacceptable performance described in section 4303, is supported by substantial evidence; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdfc-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in any other case, is supported by a preponderance of the evidence.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdfd-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding paragraph (1), the agency’s decision may not be sustained under subsection (b) of this section if the employee or applicant for employment—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdfe-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shows harmful error in the application of the agency’s procedures in arriving at such decision;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fdff-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shows that the decision was based on any prohibited personnel practice described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s2302/b"},"text":"section 2302(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe00-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shows that the decision was not in accordance with law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe01-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe02-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" In any case in which—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe03-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/d/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the interpretation or application of any civil service law, rule, or regulation, under the jurisdiction of the Office of Personnel Management is at issue in any proceeding under this section; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe04-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/d/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Director of the Office of Personnel Management is of the opinion that an erroneous decision would have a substantial impact on any civil service law, rule, or regulation under the jurisdiction of the Office;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the Director may as a matter of right intervene or otherwise participate in that proceeding before the Board. If the Director exercises his right to participate in a proceeding before the Board, he shall do so as early in the proceeding as practicable. Nothing in this title shall be construed to permit the Office to interfere with the independent decisionmaking of the Merit Systems Protection Board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe05-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Board shall promptly notify the Director whenever the interpretation of any civil service law, rule, or regulation under the jurisdiction of the Office is at issue in any proceeding under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe06-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe07-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s7702"},"text":"section 7702 of this title","children":[],"tail":", any decision under subsection (b) of this section shall be final unless—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe08-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/e/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a party to the appeal or the Director petitions the Board for review within 30 days after the receipt of the decision; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe09-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/e/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Board reopens and reconsiders a case on its own motion.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"The Board, for good cause shown, may extend the 30-day period referred to in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph. One member of the Board may grant a petition or otherwise direct that a decision be reviewed by the full Board. The preceding sentence shall not apply if, by law, a decision of an administrative law judge is required to be acted upon by the Board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0a-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Director may petition the Board for a review under paragraph (1) of this subsection only if the Director is of the opinion that the decision is erroneous and will have a substantial impact on any civil service law, rule, or regulation under the jurisdiction of the Office.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Board, or an administrative law judge or other employee of the Board designated to hear a case, may—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" consolidate appeals filed by two or more appellants, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" join two or more appeals filed by the same appellant and hear and decide them concurrently,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"if the deciding official or officials hearing the cases are of the opinion that the action could result in the appeals’ being processed more expeditiously and would not adversely affect any party.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe0f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/g/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Board, or an administrative law judge or other employee of the Board designated to hear a case, may require payment by the agency involved of reasonable attorney fees incurred by an employee or applicant for employment if the employee or applicant is the prevailing party and the Board, administrative law judge, or other employee (as the case may be) determines that payment by the agency is warranted in the interest of justice, including any case in which a prohibited personnel practice was engaged in by the agency or any case in which the agency’s action was clearly without merit.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe10-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/g/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If an employee or applicant for employment is the prevailing party and the decision is based on a finding of discrimination prohibited under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s2302/b/1"},"text":"section 2302(b)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the payment of attorney fees shall be in accordance with the standards prescribed under section 706(k) of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2000e–5/k"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 2000e–5(k)","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe11-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Board may, by regulation, provide for one or more alternative methods for settling matters subject to the appellate jurisdiction of the Board which shall be applicable at the election of an applicant for employment or of an employee who is not in a unit for which a labor organization is accorded exclusive recognition, and shall be in lieu of other procedures provided for under this section. A decision under such a method shall be final, unless the Board reopens and reconsiders a case at the request of the Office of Personnel Management under subsection (e) of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe12-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe13-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/i/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Upon the submission of any appeal to the Board under this section, the Board, through reference to such categories of cases, or other means, as it determines appropriate, shall establish and announce publicly the date by which it intends to complete action on the matter. Such date shall assure expeditious consideration of the appeal, consistent with the interests of fairness and other priorities of the Board. If the Board fails to complete action on the appeal by the announced date, and the expected delay will exceed 30 days, the Board shall publicly announce the new date by which it intends to complete action on the appeal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe14-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/i/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Not later than March 1 of each year, the Board shall submit to the Congress a report describing the number of appeals submitted to it during the preceding fiscal year, the number of appeals on which it completed action during that year, and the number of instances during that year in which it failed to conclude a proceeding by the date originally announced, together with an explanation of the reasons therefor.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe15-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/i/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Board shall by rule indicate any other category of significant Board action which the Board determines should be subject to the provisions of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe16-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/i/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" It shall be the duty of the Board, an administrative law judge, or employee designated by the Board to hear any proceeding under this section to expedite to the extent practicable that proceeding.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe17-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/j"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"j"},"text":"(j)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In determining the appealability under this section of any case involving a removal from the service (other than the removal of a reemployed annuitant), neither an individual’s status under any retirement system established by or under Federal statute nor any election made by such individual under any such system may be taken into account.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe18-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7701/k"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"k"},"text":"(k)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Board may prescribe regulations to carry out the purpose of this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8b6fe19-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/530"},"text":"80 Stat. 530","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/tII/s205"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454, title II, § 205","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","chil