 “reasonable rules and” in the phrase “reasonable rules and regulations” are omitted as unnecessary. The word “proper” in the phrase “proper administrative officer” is omitted as unnecessary. The word “designated” in the phrase “designated representative” is omitted as unnecessary."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Standard changes are made to conform with the definitions applicable and the style of this title outlined in preface to the report.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8b6fe1d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8b6fe1e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (c)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of subpar. (A) by striking “or removal from the Senior Executive Service for failure to be recertified under section 3393a”, was executed by striking out “or a removal from the Senior Executive Service for failure to be recertified under section 3393a” after “section 4303” to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (c)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/378"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–378","children":[],"tail":" amended subpar. (A) generally. Prior to amendment, subpar. (A) read as follows: “in the case of an action based on unacceptable performance described in section 4303 or a removal from the Senior Executive Service for failure to be recertified under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3393a"},"text":"section 3393a of this title","children":[],"tail":", is supported by substantial evidence, or”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsec. (b)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/175"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–175","children":[],"tail":" added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (c)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/280"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–280","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/194"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–194","children":[],"tail":", see 1989 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (j), (k). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/376"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–376","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (j) and redesignated former subsec. (j) as (k)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/12"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–12","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1) and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/194"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–194","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/280"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–280","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “or a removal from the Senior Executive Service for failure to be recertified under section 3393a of” for “of”, was executed by making the substitution for the second reference to “of” as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (i)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/386"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–386","children":[],"tail":" substituted “fiscal” for “calendar”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1979—Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/54/s2/a/45/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–54, § 2(a)(45)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “administrative” for “administration”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/54/s2/a/45/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–54, § 2(a)(45)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “(as the case may be)” for “, as the case may be,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/54/s2/a/45/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–54, § 2(a)(45)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “subsection (e)” for “subsection (d)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Appellate procedures” for “Appeals of preference eligibles” in section catchline, and in text substituted provisions relating to procedures applicable with respect to the Merit Systems Protection Board for an employee or applicant for employment, for provisions relating to appeals of preference eligible employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8b6fe1f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8b6fe20-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2002 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":" effective 60 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296/s4"},"te